{"TopicId":163689,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Long burn times ship [RO/RSS]","CreatedByName":"Mr. Sandman","CreatedById":177086,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-25T19:44:43Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Sandman","CreatedById":177086,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-25T19:44:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve built a big ship for a manned travel to Mars.It\u0027s powered by 3 nuclear engines with Liquid Hydrogen as fuel.The complessive burn time is around 2 hours and the fuel is just enough to the whole trip to Mars and return ( no errors or DeltaV waste possible).So , what\u0027s the best way to save as much DeltaV as possible in maneuvers\u00A0 by doing them efficently?Are there any rules that I have to know on how to save fuel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ship plays a lot on throwing away empty tanks ( life support and fuel), squeezing DeltaV to make the vehicle lighter.Start mass : 600 tons. End mass (from Mars to Earth): 150-200 tons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-25T20:32:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA series of periapsis kicks (\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EMangalyaan maneuver)\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis probably the best option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you prefer a more manual method and perhaps see the math:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/98843-precomputed-low-twr-interplanetary-transfer-burns/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=1701751\u0026amp;embedComment=1701751\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-1701751\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want a mod for it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/132209-122-maneuver-node-splitter-v170/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-25T20:32:53Z\u0022 title=\u002207/25/2017 08:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 25, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by regex\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aegolius13","CreatedById":165625,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-25T21:06:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might be able to save a little delta v by doing a gravity assist around the moon on your way out, but you have to hit it pretty accurately to make it worthwhile. Periapsis kicks are a good idea whether or not you plan to try this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Sandman","CreatedById":177086,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-26T14:28:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223131096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501014736\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022regex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, regex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA series of periapsis kicks (\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EMangalyaan maneuver)\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis probably the best option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you prefer a more manual method and perhaps see the math:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/98843-precomputed-low-twr-interplanetary-transfer-burns/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=1701751\u0